  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-dr-01",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. The primary hemolysis validation result (VR-01) demonstrates mean NIH error of 4.7% against the FDA benchmark dataset, satisfying the 10% acceptance criterion. The pressure-head validation (VR-02) confirms adequate bulk flow representation. The credibility evidence is assessed as sufficient to support the claim that the CFD model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The validation team noted that VR-01 was generated under build rc2 rather than the released build ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7, but concluded that the patch-level change between rc2 and the final release does not affect solver fidelity for hemolysis prediction, and that re-execution of the full validation campaign was not warranted. Overall credibility assessment: Medium. Decision: Accepted.",
